Steps to install OpenHAB in folder from: http://www.instructables.com/id/OpenHAB-on-Raspberry-Pi/
                                         http://www.openhab.org/getting-started/
                                         http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/getting-started-openhab-home-automation-raspberry-pi/

Install by running Install.sh

Make sure matchbox-window-manager and epiphany-browser is installed first (Included with BlockComPi Software)
Also Make sure PiTFT is setup as it runs on PiTFT
Run xinit ./WebUI.sh to start X11 UI

Make sure BlockComPi Software is installed first to run full config software
Run OpenHABUI.py in folder as root to start full config software

Done by Terence Chan Zun Mun with no licence (too lazy and useless to include one)